**Issue:** Intermittent 'System.ArgumentException' when Rendering GetProbabilityCurve() in Histogram

**ScottPlot Version:** 4.1.70

**Code Sample:** 

I am encountering a System.ArgumentException: 'Parameter is not valid.' during the rendering of a probability curve in a histogram plot. This exception occurs sporadically, sometimes after a few iterations and sometimes after tens of iterations. It seems to be triggered by certain combinations of mean, stdDev, min, and max values. The exception occurs at the plt.Render() line in Visual Studio and is not caught by a try-catch block. This issue appears to be related to the GetProbabilityCurve() method when scaleToBinnedProbability is set to true.

The following code generates a series of histograms with random parameters and plots their probability curves. The exception is thrown at the plt.Render() line.

```cs
Random rand = new Random(); 
for (int i = 0; i < 1000; i++)  
{
    try
    {
        var plt = new ScottPlot.Plot(600, 400);

        // Generate random values for mean, standard deviation, min, and max
        double mean = rand.NextDouble() * 198 - 99;     // Random mean between -99 and 99
        double stdDev = rand.NextDouble() * 10;         // Random stdDev between 0 and 10
        double min = rand.NextDouble() * -98.9 - 0.1;   // Random min between -99 and -0.1
        double max = rand.NextDouble() * 98.9 + 0.1;    // Random max between 0.1 and 99

        double[] values = ScottPlot.DataGen.RandomNormal(rand, pointCount: 10, mean: mean, stdDev: stdDev);

        var hist = new ScottPlot.Statistics.Histogram(min, max, binCount: 20);
        plt.AddFunction(hist.GetProbabilityCurve(values, true), System.Drawing.Color.Blue, 1);

        plt.Title("Probability Density Function");
        plt.XLabel("Value");
        plt.YLabel("Density");
        plt.Render();  
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"Exception in iteration {i}: {ex.Message}");
    }
}
```

```cs
plt.Render();
>> System.ArgumentException: 'Parameter is not valid.'
```
**An interesting observation**
Setting scaleToBinnedProbability to false in the GetProbabilityCurve() seems to prevent the exception from occurring:

```cs
plt.AddFunction(hist.GetProbabilityCurve(values, false), System.Drawing.Color.Blue, 1);
```
I suspect there might be an issue in how scaleToBinnedProbability = true is handled within GetProbabilityCurve().

